Here Antipho again makes his appearance, reflecting on the different situation of his own affairs from those of his friend Phaedria. He rejoices at his friend·s success but cannot avoid repining at his own fate, in having thus subjected him to misfortunes‚ that he found it so difficult to extricate himself from. However, he comforts himself in the best manner he can, with the small hopes that still· remain of his being able to get the better of all these threatening disasters.
